summary: This is an external email regarding a call about discovery issues in the Maxwell case, involving the US Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USAO SDNY), the FBI, and a contractor. It indicates coordination on legal matters related to discovery in the prosecution of Ghislaine Maxwell.

events.title: Call on Maxwell Discovery Issues
events.description: A scheduled call to discuss discovery issues in the Ghislaine Maxwell case, involving the US Attorney's Office, FBI, and a contractor.

keyFacts: The email is from May 21, 2021, during the pre-trial phase of Ghislaine Maxwell's prosecution.
The subject indicates ongoing discovery issues in the Maxwell case that required coordination between prosecutors and investigators.
The email is marked as external, suggesting communication between the US Attorney's Office and an outside party, likely a contractor (PAE).
The distribution list includes multiple recipients from the US Attorney's Office and the FBI, indicating a multi-agency discussion.
The document reference EFTA00154981 is part of the Epstein case files released by the Department of Justice.
